casebody.data:
Pete HARMON v. UNITED STATES of America. No., 2087. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. June 19, 1940. Ward, Justus & Ward, of Tulsa, Old., for appellant. Whit Y. Mauzy, U. S. Atty., of Tulsa, Old., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS and BRATTON, Circuit Judges, and MURRAH, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed, on motion of appellee at appellant’s costs, for failure to prosecute.
